public int getImageHeight ()

Returns the instrument cluster's supported image height.

The height of the image sent in the TurnEvent of sendTurnEvent(TurnEvent) should not be different than this size. If the height of that image does not match this value, the entire TurnEvent message will be dropped.

Returns
int

public int getImageWidth ()

Returns the instrument cluster's supported image width.

The width of the image sent in the TurnEvent of sendTurnEvent(TurnEvent) should not be different than this size. If the width of that image does not match this value, the entire TurnEvent message will be dropped.

Returns
int

public int getMinMessageIntervalMs ()

Returns the minimum amount of time (in ms) that must be between messages sent with sendTurnEvent(TurnEvent) to the car's instrument cluster.

This field can be ignored by navigation providers. Android Auto automatically rate limits messages sent to it via sendTurnEvent(), so navigation providers do not need to implement this logic.

Returns
int

public boolean supportsImages ()

Returns true if this instrument cluster can display images supplied by the navigation provider.

If this is false, images should not be supplied in a TurnEvent sent via sendTurnEvent(TurnEvent).

Returns
boolean

protected void writeToBundle (Bundle bundle)

Writes the states of the instance to the given Bundle. Only primitives or system classes can be written into the Bundle. If a field of a custom class needs to be serialized, serialize it into a new Bundle and then write that Bundle into the outer Bundle. A list or array of custom class instances should similarly be converted into an array of Bundles first.

bundle Bundle
